args:
With Alberius defeated, the prince swears to
carry on his will. But after Morsayati regains
his full power, he convinces the prince's
siblings to join his malicious cause.
Freedom...at long last...\nAnd yet my duty is incomplete...
Enough, Your Majesty. You fought and\nsuffered to the very end; you have done\nmore than enough.
Cleo's right. The people of this world\nbelieved in you, and you repaid that\nfaith by granting them peace.
I swear to you here and now, we will never\nlet the hope you've given us be wasted.
I stand before you, O king.
I wish for you to have the power\nentrusted me by Chthonius...
I shall protect this powerful mana for all\ntime in the form of a shadow dracolith.
So you are finally shuffling off this mortal\ncoil, eh, Alberius? How sad that you must\nfall by the hand of your own descendants!
Allow me to thank you for putting an end\nto Alberius, dear brother.
I want no thanks from you!

Still, with that dragon defeated, you will
probably want an explanation about what
happened to the portion of me that was
trapped inside Alberius, mmm?
But now that Alberius is gone,\nthat should be...
Oh, but this is simply TOO much, Brother.\nDid you truly think that would be enough\nto destroy the majesty that is me?!
Did you actually believe your meager\nstrength would be enough to defeat\nthe essence of all that I am?!
It's Morsayati's core what we saw in the\nmonument vision!
And now, at long last, the greatest part\nof me can finally return to the whole!
Behold the hour of my rebirth!
It has been so very long... Ha ha!\nAaaaaah ha ha ha ha ha!
At last, I am whole once more!
By the goddess, his mana is ghastly!
My body shakes... My hands tremble...\nFie, but I fear this thing down to the\nvery depths of my soul...
Just lookin' at it makes me\nwanna pass out...
I think I'm gonna hurl, guys...
I know well that the body before us\nwas once that of the Auspex.

But I cannot stand idly by and do nothing
with this monster possessing the full
measure of its power. For the sake of
the vow I swore long ago, I must act!
Aaaah ha ha! Oh, what a mother hen\nyou are, my dear brother!
I told you, I am whole once more.\nBut perhaps you need to be shown\nprecisely what this means...
You should have simply obeyed me,\nShadowwyrm. But now, your only\nreward will be pain!
He took Zodiark down with a single blow...
Disappointing, Shadowwyrm.\nThat wasn't even half my power.
Feel the depths of your foolishness for\ndaring to raise your hand against me!\nReturn to nothingness! Return to DUST!
No! I won't let you do that!
Ha ha ha ha! You would stand in my way\neven knowing the full extent of my power?\nI am almost impressed, little prince.
Therefore, I give you an opportunity:\nSwear fealty to me and live.
Why would I ever do that?!
Oh, and this is an open offer to both\nyou AND all of your siblings.
Leonidas, you can't be considering this!
To stand supreme astride the world,\none must possess the greatest power IN\nthat world. I have always thought thus.
So you'll serve a tyrant just because\nthey have power?!

I serve no one—I simply fight at their side
in order to lay waste to the old ways.
Once this is concluded, we will surely
vie for supremacy.

I have no interest in either a kingdom
or the concepts of good and evil.
I seek only to follow the path that
satisfies my inquiring mind.
Chelle! You said you'd cooperate with us,\nremember?! Surely you won't do this!
I said that in PRIVATE, dear brother! *sigh*\nYou have much to learn about diplomacy.
Sadly, no promise lasts forever.\nLet that be your lesson for the day.
And Valyx! You would obey the Empire\neven knowing the truth of the Other?
And a world ruled by inviolable, absolute\npower is a peaceful one...in its own way.
Emile! This can't be what you want!
I'll not be lectured by someone of\nYOUR standing, {player_name}!
Every last one of you has treated me\nlike a piece of moldy gutter trash!
The Other can smash this world to bits\nfor all that I care!
Do you see the truth of it now,\n{player_name}? You stand alone.
It...it doesn't matter! I will carry on\nAlberius's will! I will bring peace to—
I believe you misunderstand my goals.\nYou mortals are free to have whatever\nkind of peace you desire.

Despite what you seem to think, I do not
wish to inflict suffering upon people.
In truth, I am rather indifferent to the
joy or pain of your individual lives.
But if seeing your fellow mortals enjoy\na free and happy life is important to you,\nI could easily see this thing done.
Oh, sure! Like we'd believe THAT\nline of crap comin' from you!

Do you feel empathy for every gnat that
lives in your forest, sylvan? Do you
invest yourself fully in the existence
of each worm that crawls in the dirt?

I hate to agree with this guy when he's
bein' a total jackass, but he might have
a point. I mean, to him, we mortal types
ain't nothin' more than ants, yeah?
If you wish it to be done, I will order all\nfiends to stand down and end any\nremaining human conflicts.

This perfect world is yours for the taking,
and it will cost nothing but your reverence.
What possible reason could you have to
refuse this offer?
Surely this is what your sister\ndesires as well, yes?
I would hear your response now.\nWill you swear all fealty to me?\nWill you revere me above all others?
What? Why would you fight me when\nI have offered you a perfect world?
Because the world won't be perfect\nif Zethia isn't in it!
You would cast aside true peace for all\ncreatures of the world in exchange\nfor the life of a single person?
Zethia means absolutely everything to me,\nand I could never live in a kingdom built\non the bones and ashes of her sacrifice.
I desire to live in a world where people\nprotect those they love!
I won't live in a world where people are\nforced to crawl upon their knees in order\nto seek out YOUR protection!
I'll never agree to a world like that!
Aaaah ha ha ha! Oh, but you DO\nresemble Alberius right now.
Henceforth, you will face off against\nall those with whom you share blood!
Be that as it may, I WILL save this world.
What magnificent resolve! But let's see\nif you can even flee this particular area\nbefore we start talking about ＂the world.＂
Hmm. Perhaps it would be best for me\nto end this here and now.
Entrust the future of this world to\nyour dear sister, {player_name}!\nEntrust it to ME!
I will not...let the light of hope fade...\nWith what power remains to me...\nI will spirit you away from this place...
Let go, old man. The more you hang on, \nthe more you suffer.
Urrgh! I leave this world to you,\n{player_name}!
And I WILL protect the dream\nyou fought so long for!
...Hmph. An unexpected trifle, but a trifle\nnonetheless.
Besides, it should make for fine sport\nto watch this family tear itself apart!
Come, descendants of Alberius!\nFollow your new master!
AAAAH HA HA HA HA HA!
